ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.deer_antler.description=Dropped by deer. (Will be tradeable in a future update.)
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.deer_hide.description=Dropped by deer. (Will be tradeable in a future update.)
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.dweller_flesh.description=Dropped by Dwellers, can be used in a funrace to get leather.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.aloe_vera.description=Dropped by mining an Aloe Vera plant. Can be eaten.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.coconut.description=Dropped by mining coconuts found on palm trees. Can be split in any crafting grid to eat, or be thrown.\n\nCoconuts can be used to craft Coconut Palm Saplings, which can then be planted to grow more Coconut Palms.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.banana.description=Dropped by Banana Blocks that grow on Banana Trees, which are rarely found in jungle biomes. Very nutricius!
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.banana_seeds.description=Sometimes dropped by Banana Blocks, use it to craft Banana Tree Saplings, which can be planted to grow more Banana Trees.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.grizzly_pelt.description=Dropped by grizzly bears. (Will be tradeable in a future update.)
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.lurker_foot.description=Dropped rarely by lurkers, use it to craft swiftrunner boots.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.swiftrunner_boots.description=Special gear created using lurkers' feet and dwellers' flesh. Wear it to be granted with speed!
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.sulfur.description=Dropped by mining Sulfur Ore. Can be used to craft gunpowder, used as a fuel source, or crafted into a bag of sulfur.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.raw_tungsten.description=Dropped by mining Tungsten Ore. Can be smelted in a furnace to obtain Tungsten Ingots.
ui.biomes_beyond.wiki.tungsten_ingot.description=Obtained from smelting raw Tungsten in a furnace.

